14 PART XIV. LOUISIANA COMMISSION ON FOUNDATIONAL EDUCATION
15 §410.21. Louisiana Commission on Foundational Education
16 A. The Louisiana Commission on Foundational Education, referred to in this
17 Section as the "commission", is hereby created for the purpose of evaluating and
18 making recommendations to improve foundational education policy.
19 B. The commission has the following powers and duties:
20 (1) To serve as an advisory body to the State Board of Elementary and
21 Secondary Education and the state Department of Education on matters relating to
22 foundational literacy, numeracy, and family engagement from kindergarten through
23 grade eight.
24 (2) To research and analyze all policies, regulations, procedures, and funding
25 structures relative to the implementation of foundational education initiatives,
26 reforms, and instructional practices.
